begin_memory_text: We talked about what we do for work, where we live, etc. He asked how long I've been doing my job and explained what he does for his job.
middle_memory_text: He shared some of his sex/relationship problems and I offered a bit of advice. He shared that he has low sexual desire and needs a lot of novelty.
end_memory_text: At the end we talked about age and how there have been times we don't feel our age. He shared that all his friends are young and women his age don't get him.
rest_of_day_open: It's finally the weekend! Tonight I'm looking forward to chilling out and doing some art, and then tomorrow I'm hanging out with my daughter and then my partner is coming over and we're going to carve pumpkins. I've been really emotionally depleted this week but I'm glad it's the weekend.
critical_positive: It worked well that we immediately had things in common. It worked that he was willing to be open and vulnerable about the things he struggles with. He asked me some questions about myself, which I appreciated. He was not afraid to talk, that's for sure! He was very talkative.
critical_negative: It didn't work well that he took the most control over the conversation. Once I mentioned I'm a sex therapist, he noted a couple of times that he could use some sex advice, and eventually I offered because I didn't know what else to talk about, but then he seemed reluctant to take any of my advice, which was annoying.
